    "body": "### Problem\n\n_I've reported this in [zellij](https://github.com/zellij-org/zellij/) as well, so this description is some what duplicate_\n\n(a little context:)\nSo I was using nvim 0.10.3 until now.\nI've upgraded to nightly a few days ago and current version is ` v0.11.0-dev-1627+g2470db02c5`.\nBut I've encountered a problem that wasn't there before.\nMy main language is Persian, so all the messages in the code that I work on is Persian.\nI use ZWNJ character a lot in my code and in `nvim 0.10.3`, it was shown as `<200c>` and I could easily find it:\n\n\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cc16793d-0c47-4b18-ad8a-93b086fb2c15)\n\nIn `nightly` however, it has changed to the real value and renders <c200> and it behaves as the real ZWNJ, like this: \n\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7fcbb3ae-eecd-41fa-bd0f-06c7beda15f0)\n\n\nBut the problem is that the latest, doesn't work in zellij.\nIn zellij, it doesn't show at all and the characters aren't separated anymore:\n\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0251b4b4-7bc6-4b26-91be-3e6598c50a1b)\n\nSo with this change, zellij cannot show the character and it creates a lot of problems for me.\n\nThis is the text in the pictures: `شناسه‌ها`\n\nIs there anyway to revert back this change in neovim?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:lua vim.opt.termbidi = true\nwrite this: \"شناسه‌ها\"\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should show as `شناسه<c200>ها`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-1627+g2470db02c5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI don't think so\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.13.2-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20241031-235112-0983ae90\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nneovim-nightly-bin",
