            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yeah, if we don't implement unicode because `$OTHER_SOFTWARE` does not implement it, it will just lead to deadlock, as `$OTHER_SOFTWARE` can just reason the same way and not implement unicode because apps in the nvim layer of things doesn't. \n\nSometimes there are de facto ambiguities were the unicode standard is imprecise, which are going to need to be resolved (like `setcellwidth()`,  https://github.com/kovidgoyal/kitty/issues/8226, etc), but the meaning of \"real ZWNJ\" is pretty clear and precisely implemented by nvim. In those cases, the path forward is to file a bug to the other party, just like clason said.",
